					<head>Arukh by Nathan ben Jehiel of Rome (vol. 1)</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85059886" rend="visible">
						<summary>A talmudic lexicon, volume 1.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="149v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">῾Arukh</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ערוך</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="viaf.org/viaf/88359528">Nathan ben Jehiel, of Rome </persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/88359528">נתן בן יחיאל, מרומה</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Incomplete at the end. </p>
								<p>Each section deals with an entire letter of the alphabet, and is divided into chapters. The first section is preceded by a list giving the number of chapters in each of the twenty-two sections, and noting combinations of of letters not extant in the lexicon. </p>
								<p>Volume 1 ends with the beginning of the article on כלבום, continuing without a break at the opening of volume 2. </p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Uniform with Or 1265 (volume 2 of the same work). Cf. the contents of Add MS 26881.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment and paper codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="mixed">
								<support>Parchment and paper. </support>
								<extent>149 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>345</height>
										<width>270</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>300</height>
										<width>200</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>149 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and 2 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>8 quires of 16 to 20 leaves each (the first quire missing a few leaves). Inner and outer leaf of each quire is parchment. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Tidemark at head, sometimes at edges. </p>
									<p>Front paper leaves repaired/infilled before rebinding. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="39" writtenLines="39">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Many leaves irregularly shaped. </p>
									<p>Initial and final words in square characters, headings in square characters and partly in red ink. </p>
									<p>Marginal and in-between columns notes.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
